## 9. DevOps, CI/CD & Deployment

### 9.1 Docker Setup

```yaml
# docker-compose.yml (target)
services:
  frontend:
    build: ./client
    ports: ["3000:3000"]
    depends_on: [backend]

  backend:
    build: ./server
    ports: ["5000:5000"]
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://user:pass@db:5432/elms
      REDIS_URL: redis://redis:6379
      JWT_SECRET: ${JWT_SECRET}
      GEMINI_API_KEY: ${GEMINI_API_KEY}
    depends_on: [db, redis]

  db:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    volumes: ["pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data"]
    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: elms
      POSTGRES_USER: user
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: pass

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine

  nginx:
    image: nginx:alpine
    ports: ["80:80", "443:443"]
    volumes: ["./nginx.conf:/etc/nginx/nginx.conf"]
    depends_on: [frontend, backend]

volumes:
  pgdata:
```

### 9.2 CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)

```
Trigger: Push to main or PR
│
├── 🔍 Lint (ESLint + Prettier)
├── 🧪 Unit Tests (Vitest)
├── 🧪 Integration Tests (Supertest + Test DB)
├── 🏗️ Build (Vite production build)
├── 🐳 Docker Build + Push to Registry
├── 🚀 Deploy to Staging (auto)
├── ✅ E2E Tests on Staging (Playwright)
└── 🚀 Deploy to Production (manual approval)
```

### 9.3 Deployment Options

| Environment | Option | Cost Estimate |
|------------|--------|---------------|
| **Free Tier** | Vercel (frontend) + Railway (backend) + Neon (DB) | $0/mo |
| **Budget** | DigitalOcean App Platform | $12-25/mo |
| **Mid-range** | AWS ECS + RDS + ElastiCache | $50-100/mo |
| **Enterprise** | Kubernetes (EKS/GKE) | $200+/mo |

---

## 10. Testing Strategy

### 10.1 Testing Pyramid

| Layer | Tool | Coverage Target | What to Test |
|-------|------|----------------|--------------|
| **Unit Tests** | Vitest | 80% | Utility functions, validators, hooks |
| **Component Tests** | Vitest + Testing Library | 70% | React components in isolation |
| **API Integration Tests** | Supertest + Vitest | 90% | Every API endpoint |
| **E2E Tests** | Playwright | Key flows | Login → Apply → Approve → Verify |
| **Performance Tests** | k6 / Artillery | Baseline | API response times under load |

### 10.2 Key Test Scenarios

```
Auth:
  ✓ Register with valid data → 201
  ✓ Register with duplicate email → 409
  ✓ Login with correct credentials → 200 + JWT
  ✓ Login with wrong password → 401
  ✓ Access protected route without JWT → 401
  ✓ Access admin route as employee → 403
  ✓ Refresh expired token → new tokens

Leave Management:
  ✓ Apply leave within balance → 201
  ✓ Apply leave exceeding balance → 400
  ✓ Apply overlapping leave → 400
  ✓ Approve pending leave → status changes to Approved
  ✓ Reject pending leave → status changes to Rejected
  ✓ Edit pending leave → updated
  ✓ Edit approved leave → 403
  ✓ Manager approves own leave → 403
  ✓ Leave balance decremented after approval
  ✓ Notification sent on status change

E2E Flows:
  ✓ Employee Login → Apply Leave → See in Dashboard
  ✓ Admin Login → View Pending → Approve → Employee sees updated status
  ✓ Employee tries to access admin page → redirected
  ✓ Full CRUD on employees (admin)
  ✓ View analytics charts with data
```

---

## 11. Phase-wise Implementation Plan

### 📅 Phase 1: Core Backend + Auth (Weeks 1–3)

**Week 1: Project Setup & Database**
- [ ] Initialize backend with Express + TypeScript (optional) structure
- [ ] Set up Prisma with PostgreSQL
- [ ] Create all database migrations (users, roles, departments, leave_types)
- [ ] Seed database with initial data (admin user, departments, leave types)
- [ ] Set up environment variables and configs
- [ ] Create Docker Compose for local development

**Week 2: Auth & User Management**
- [ ] Implement registration endpoint with email verification
- [ ] Implement login endpoint with JWT access + refresh tokens
- [ ] Implement password reset flow
- [ ] Create auth middleware (JWT verification)
- [ ] Create RBAC middleware (role-based permission checks)
- [ ] Implement user CRUD endpoints (admin)
- [ ] Set up Nodemailer for transactional emails

**Week 3: Frontend Auth Integration**
- [ ] Replace mock auth in frontend with real API calls
- [ ] Add Axios instance with interceptors (auto-attach JWT, auto-refresh)
- [ ] Implement React Query for server state management
- [ ] Add login/register/forgot-password pages
- [ ] Add loading/skeleton screens
- [ ] Add Error Boundaries

### 📅 Phase 2: Leave Management System (Weeks 4–6)

**Week 4: Leave Core**
- [ ] Leave CRUD API endpoints
- [ ] Leave balance calculation service
- [ ] Leave validation (overlap check, balance check, date validation)
- [ ] Leave approval workflow (approve/reject with reason)
- [ ] Connect frontend leave form to API
- [ ] Connect frontend leave table to API with pagination

**Week 5: Leave Enhancements**
- [ ] Leave policy engine (accrual rules, carry-over, encashment)
- [ ] Holiday management (CRUD + calendar integration)
- [ ] Half-day / hourly leave support
- [ ] Document attachment upload (multer + S3)
- [ ] Leave calendar view (frontend with FullCalendar or custom)

**Week 6: Notifications**
- [ ] Email notifications on leave status changes
- [ ] In-app notification system (database + API)
- [ ] Real-time notifications via WebSocket (Socket.io)
- [ ] Notification center UI (bell icon + dropdown + page)

### 📅 Phase 3: People & Organization (Weeks 7–9)

**Week 7: Department & Hierarchy**
- [ ] Department CRUD (backend + frontend admin page)
- [ ] Manager-subordinate relationship
- [ ] Multi-level approval routing based on hierarchy
- [ ] Department-scoped leave views

**Week 8: Employee Management**
- [ ] Employee directory page (search, filter, pagination)
- [ ] Employee detail page (profile + leave history + balance)
- [ ] Employee profile editing (self-service)
- [ ] Bulk import via CSV upload
- [ ] Profile picture upload

**Week 9: Manager Role**
- [ ] Manager dashboard (team overview)
- [ ] Team calendar (who's on leave today)
- [ ] Quick approve/reject from manager dashboard
- [ ] Manager-specific reporting

### 📅 Phase 4: Analytics & AI (Weeks 10–13)

**Week 10: Analytics Dashboard**
- [ ] Install Recharts for charting
- [ ] Department-wise leave distribution (pie chart)
- [ ] Leave type distribution (bar chart)
- [ ] Monthly leave trends (line chart)
- [ ] Top leave-takers table
- [ ] Date range filter for all charts

**Week 11: Reports & Export**
- [ ] Report generation service (backend)
- [ ] CSV export of leave data
- [ ] PDF report generation (pdfkit or Puppeteer)
- [ ] Scheduled report emails (weekly/monthly to admin)
- [ ] Custom report builder (select columns, filters, date range)

**Week 12: AI Integration**
- [ ] Set up Gemini API client on backend
- [ ] Build AI Chatbot endpoint with context injection
- [ ] Create chatbot UI component (floating widget + full page)
- [ ] Build leave prediction endpoint
- [ ] Create prediction visualization on admin dashboard

**Week 13: AI Advanced**
- [ ] Anomaly detection service
- [ ] Anomaly alerts on admin dashboard
- [ ] Smart leave date suggestions
- [ ] AI insights widget on employee dashboard
- [ ] Audit trail implementation

### 📅 Phase 5: Production & Polish (Weeks 14–16)

**Week 14: Security & Performance**
- [ ] Add Helmet.js, CORS, rate limiting
- [ ] Implement Redis caching for policies/holidays
- [ ] Add database indexes for performance
- [ ] Frontend code splitting (React.lazy per route)
- [ ] Bundle optimization (tree shaking, lazy imports)
- [ ] Account lockout on failed attempts

**Week 15: Testing & Quality**
- [ ] Write unit tests for backend services (80% coverage)
- [ ] Write API integration tests (90% coverage)
- [ ] Write component tests for critical UI components
- [ ] Write E2E tests for key user flows (Playwright)
- [ ] Accessibility audit + fixes (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- [ ] Set up dark/light theme toggle

**Week 16: DevOps & Launch**
- [ ] Production Dockerfiles (multi-stage builds)
- [ ] Docker Compose for production
- [ ] Nginx reverse proxy with SSL
- [ ] GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline
- [ ] Prometheus metrics + Grafana dashboards
- [ ] Winston structured logging
- [ ] Health check endpoints
- [ ] Deploy to production
- [ ] Post-launch monitoring setup

